<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">About Konomi Standard</h1>

<div class="space-y-6 text-konomi-text">
  <section>
    <h2 class="section-heading">What is Konomi Standard?</h2>
    <p class="text-konomi-muted">
      Konomi Standard is a self-defining industrial standards compression format. It provides a
      unified way to represent and work with multiple industrial automation standards including
      ISA-95, ISA-88, ISA-101, ISA-18.2, OPC-UA, MQTT Sparkplug, Modbus, and KPI metrics.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="section-heading">Key Features</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-konomi-muted">
      <li>UDT-first design: Everything defined as User Defined Types</li>
      <li>Self-describing: Layer 0 defines how all other layers are structured</li>
      <li>Crosswalks: Built-in mappings between different standards</li>
      <li>Compression: Maximum information in minimum tokens</li>
      <li>Hierarchical: Clear layering from meta-standard to specific protocols</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="section-heading">Layer Architecture</h2>
    <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
      <div class="udt-field"><span class="text-konomi-accent">Layer 0:</span> Meta-standard (how standards are defined)</div>
      <div class="udt-field"><span class="text-konomi-accent">Layer 1:</span> Base UDTs (primitives all standards use)</div>
      <div class="udt-field"><span class="text-konomi-accent">Layer 2:</span> ISA-95 (Enterprise↔Control Integration)</div>
      <div class="udt-field"><span class="text-konomi-accent">Layer 3:</span> ISA-88 (Batch Control)</div>
      <div class="udt-field"><span class="text-konomi-accent">Layer 4:</span> ISA-101 (HMI Design)</div>
      <div class="udt-field"><span class="text-konomi-accent">Layer 5:</span> ISA-18.2 (Alarm Management)</div>
      <div class="udt-field"><span class="text-konomi-accent">Layer 6:</span> OPC-UA (Communication)</div>
      <div class="udt-field"><span class="text-konomi-accent">Layer 7:</span> MQTT/Sparkplug (Messaging)</div>
      <div class="udt-field"><span class="text-konomi-accent">Layer 8:</span> Modbus (Field Protocol)</div>
      <div class="udt-field"><span class="text-konomi-accent">Layer 9:</span> KPIs (Performance Metrics)</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="section-heading">Usage</h2>
    <div class="bg-konomi-surface p-4 rounded border border-konomi-primary/30">
      <pre class="text-konomi-text text-sm"><code>from konomi_standard import KS

# Parse: human standard → compressed
compressed = KS.parse("ISA-95", source_doc)

# Expand: compressed → implementation
impl = KS.expand("ISA-95", target="python")

# Validate: impl → compliant?
report = KS.validate(impl, "ISA-95")

# Crosswalk: map between standards
mapped = KS.crosswalk(entity, "ISA-95", "ISA-88")

# Generate: template → code
code = KS.generate("ISA-88.Batch", lang="python")</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="section-heading">Goal</h2>
    <p class="text-konomi-muted">
      The goal is to create a compression format for industrial standards that is:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-konomi-muted mt-2">
      <li>Self-describing and machine-readable</li>
      <li>Compact yet comprehensive</li>
      <li>Interoperable across multiple standards</li>
      <li>Suitable for LLM context windows</li>
      <li>Executable and validatable</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</div>
